🚀 Last week, we launched the Bridge'Up training program, dedicated to supporting startups in their internationalization! 🌍

The Bridge'Up project is part of the “From Innovation to creation” program funded by the EU in cooperation with Stichting SPARK and The Dot.
We designed this program to empower entrepreneurs from Lebanon, Jordan, Palestine, and Tunisia with the essential knowledge needed to go global.

Out of 80 applicants, 35 entrepreneurs have been selected to embark on this 5-week journey filled with expert insights and practical exercises (it was a tough call as we had amazing applicants!). Congratulations to all!

Throughout this program, we will cover 5 key topics:
🔍 Week 1: Understanding Internationalization Fundamentals
📊 Week 2: Crafting Your Market Entry Strategy
📜 Week 3: Navigating Legal and Financial Realities
🌎 Week 4: Achieving Operational Excellence
🚀 Week 5: Launching Your International Journey

Stay tuned for weekly updates on our LinkedIn page. We will be sharing highlights and insights from our expert speakers.

Thank you to all the partners for this initiative: CoStarT, INJAZ Lebanon, TTi & Station J

#BridgeUp #FromInnovationToCreation #Together4med #SPARK #TheDot
#PeopleOfGrowth #Internationalization

Are you ready to drive your career forward with innovation and cutting-edge technology? Bako Motors is excited to announce internship opportunities for aspiring talents! 🌟

We're offering dynamic internship positions across various departments, from Business Development & Sales to Marketing, Engineering, and more. This is your chance to gain hands-on experience and be part of our pioneering team shaping the future of electric vehicles!

Explore our PFE Book 2023 here [link to the PFE Book] to discover the range of exciting internships we have available. 

Join us in revolutionizing the automotive industry and be at the forefront of sustainable transportation! 🚗💡

#InternshipOpportunity #BakoMotors #Innovation #FutureLeaders #CareerGrowth"

Chère communauté, accueillant de nouveaux membres dans notre famille, hier nous avons eu une journée pleine de formations afin de développer nos compétences et débloquer de nouveaux potentiels.
Partageant ces photos avec vous, nous tenons à remercier énormément monsieur Firas Bejaoui  le responsable événementiel de la Confédération Tunisienne des Junior Entreprises  2021-2022, pour la formation en Event Management, notre chère alumna madame Marzouk Nour  la présidente de la DJE 2020-2021 pour la formation en Gestion des Réseaux Sociaux, madame Molka Kouki  notre chère vice-présidente pour ce mandat et chargée de mission sponsoring au sein de la JET pour la formation en Sponsoring et Prospection et finalement madame Sahar Abid  notre chère présidente pour ce mandat pour la formation en Mailing.
Nous sommes ravis de vous annoncer que cette mission a été un succès, nous remercions également l’Université Libre de Tunis (ULT)  pour les salles des formations et nous espérons que ce mandat continuera d'être couronné de succès comme il a commencé.
